&quot;The lizard's ancestors are the cause of its being hunted.&quot;
– Abul ʿAla Al-Maʿarri&quot;

Decidedly the best application of art to industry is when a great many copies are made from an exceedingly good pattern.&quot;
–William Burges, &quot;Art applied to industry: a series of lectures&quot;, 1865. p. 1.

&quot;Effectiveness is doing the things that get you closer to your goals. Efficiency is performing a given task (whether important or not) in the most economical manner possible. Being efficient without regard to effectiveness is the default mode of the universe.&quot;
– Timothy Ferriss, &quot;The 4-Hour Workweek&quot;  (2007). 

&quot;The woodcutter is far better for skill than he is for brute strength.
It is by skill that the sea captain holds his rapid ship
on its course, though torn by winds, over the wine-blue water.
By skill charioteer outpasses charioteer.&quot;
– Homer, &quot;The Iliad&quot;, Book XXIII, lines 315–318
